              "According to the general procedure from 0.545 g diethyl 3-amino-2-hydroxypropylphosphonate (12, 2.58 mmol) and 0.642 g (5-bromouracil-1-yl) acetic acid (13c, 2.58 mmol), the amide 9c (0.552 g, 48% yield) was obtained as a white powder after purification on a silica gel column with chloroform-methanol mixtures (50:1, 20:1 v/v) and HPLC (C18 column, 25 ",
