              "According to the general procedure from 0.107 g diethyl 2-amino-1-hydroxyethylphosphonate (10, 0.543 mmol) and 0.102 g (5-fluorouracil-1-yl)acetic acid (13b, 0.543 mmol), the amide 7b (0.81 g, 41% yield) was obtained as a white powder after purification on a silica gel column with chloroform-methanol mixtures ",
